{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_beiderbecke_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280657475/1924021401/0646.xml":{"full_text":"24\nCOOLIDGE REMARKS\nON BONUS DRAW FIRE\nlegion Head Takes Issue With'\nPresident on Cost of Meas-\nure to Country.\nINSINUATION \u2018BESENTEL\u201d j\nQuinn Denies Veterans Would Eu-!\ni\ndanger U. S. Economically.\ni\nHr the Anwoeiateit I\u2019rrfH,\nINDIANAPOLIS, I ml.. February 14.\nJohn K. Quinn, national commander of\ntho American Legion, yesterday took 1\nissue with certain statements about ad- j\njusted compensation made by President\nCoolidgo in his New York speech before\nthe National Republican Club.\nIn a telegram to the President Com- I\nmandcr Quinn denied that the passage\nof an adjusted compensation bill would\nfinancially wreck the country or bring 1\nabout a business depression.\nCommander Quinn also declared that\nthe figures as to the cost of adjusted i\ncompensation used by the President in\nhis address are more than double the j\ncost estimate submitted by Treasury\nactuaries some time ago.\nResents Insinuation,\nReferring to the statement by Presi- 1\nQn W ITH 7f HE\nHere\u2019s news for men who appreciate the value of good\ni\nappearance. And tor their wives who realize that their\nhusbands are a part of the picture.\ni\nt\n\nSociety Brand Sails for Spring are in.\nHecht Cc.Saits f Spring are\n\n\nBusiness, baseball, bobolinks and red birds soon will be\nsinging their spring songs. Crocuses and golf bugs will\nI I\nbe with us. Lovely girls will promenade F street in the\n\n\u201ctailleur masculine\u201d which so accentuates their feminine\ncharm. (And they will know\nj\nji\nFor spring is in the air, and it\u2019s catching. So much so\nthat even staid, sedate, sophisticated business men will hie\nthemselves to The Hecht Co. so that they too may keep in\nstep. 1 1\nFor although clothes do not make the man\u2014the right\nones make him feel a great deal happier. He wouldn\u2019t\nadmit it. But ask his wife\u2014she knows,\n\nJ\n\nI\nSpring suits priced*2s to *75\n7th\n\ndent Coolldge tliat the welfare of the\nwhole country may be jeopardized If a\nbonus is paid, the telegram said:\n\"The man who came to the rescue of\nhis country in time of danger resents\nthe insinuation that he would endanger\nhis country In time of peace. Our sup\nport of adjusted compensation is based\nupon Justice, upon patriotic precedent\nand upon public desire as repeatedly\nI reflected by votes of Congress. We are j\nI convinced that tho payment of this Just j\nobligation would be a minor item in the i\nI nation\u2019s budget and not the tremendous\nitem created by recent Treasury esll- I\ni mates, which more than double those I\n1 originally presented to tho .Senate I\nfinance committee for the same bljl.\u201d.|\n1 The telegram continued:\n\"While you say a very large body of\nVeterans does not want the \u2018bonus.\u2019 i\ntiie distinction between a large body I\ni and a large proportion is obvious;\nand the American Legion knows that\nI it represents a tremendous majority\nI In support of the bill.\n\"We agree with you that the physl\ncally disabled should he supported,\n1 and the legion in accepting this policy\ni has already spent millions of dollars\nto insure them Justice. We further\ni agree that the American soldier did j\n1 not enter service for the purpose of\ni personal gain.\"\nBuenos Aires Enjoys Boom.\nBuenos Aires is growing faster;\nprobably than any other city in\nSouth America, and its population is\nnow said to tie beyond the 2.000,000\nmark and conditions are troublesome\nto the authorities because housing i\nlegislation cannot be executed fast\nenough to keep up w ith the strides\nof the city. Immigration from abroad\nand from other provinces is vetyi\n1 rapid.\nTHE EVENING STAR, WASHINGTON, D. 0.. THURSDAY. FEBRUARY 14, 1924.\nEgyptian Maiden 9 s Bones in Museum\nIndicate She May Have Been Executed\nDoctors at Conference Over X-rays Say However,\nShipping May Have Caused Fractures to Mummy\nof Lady Tesha of 3,000 Years Ago\u2022\ni\nmi i\ni hr the Avxnclsteil Press.\nMINNEAPOLIS, Minn., February 14.\nI\u2014A conference of doctors was called\nhere yesterday to determine whether\ni she hod been done to death after It\nj was found that Lady Tesha, daughter\n'of the doorkeeper of the Holden\ni House of Amon, dead 3,000 years, had\nhardly a whole bone In her body.\nThe body, wrapped in yards of lln\ni m. painted with gum and covered\nI with a plaster case, gaily painted, is 1\nin tlie Minneapolis Institute of Arts,\nwhere it was brought in 1910, after i\nhaving been excavated from her tomb j\nj at Thebe. Egypt, several years pre- j\ni viously.\nBecause of the unusual beauty of 1\nthe painted panels on the mummy\ncase, no effort has been made to opdn\nit, and until yesterday nothing was j\nknown of the case\u2019s contents. X-Ray 1\nplates were developed yesterday and\nshowed that the Lady Tesha\u2019s head\nwas severed from her body, and that\nseveral hones ill her arms and thorax\ni were misplaced and broken.\nAt first it was thought that fnd)-\ncated execution or murder, but a\ncouncil of physlciana advanced tho\ntheory that In the collapse of tissues\nwithin the mummy case the bones\nhad fallen away front their original\npositions, and probably were frac\ntured In transit.\nI There still Is a possibility, how\never, that buck In the twenty-first\ndynasty, where she. a maiden of four\nteen years, served her father in tho\ntreasury of Anion, the Egyptian prin\ncipal deity. Lady Tesha was crushed\nto death for a fancied wrong.\nThe Mayor\u2019s Family.\n1 From the K\u00abn<s\u00bb City Stir.\nThe mayor of a small town In Ohio\nj had six stout sons, with whotn he\ni loved to parade Main atreet. They\nfurnished him with the basis of a\nmathematical Joke. \u201cA fine family\nI you have.\" strangers would often\nsay. \u201cIs this the whole of It?\u201d \u2018\u2018No.\u201d\n1 the mayor would reply. \"Bach and\nevery son has two sisters at home.\u201d\n\"What!\"